16/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Authorities announced on Friday (August 14th) that they have deported 82 illegal immigrants from Pakistan and Afghanistan. 
The immigrants were flown home aboard charter flights. 
Most of them were Afghans, who agreed to leave Greece voluntarily. 
This is the third group of illegal immigrants deported in the past month. 
(ERT, RIA Novosti - 14/08/09)
